'''Sam Speakman''' (born 9 August 1884 in [[Liverpool]], England) was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played as a defender for [[Liverpool F.C.]] in [[The Football League]]. Speakman started his career at Colne FC before he joined Liverpool. He played primarily as a full back and made 14 appearances for the club before the outbreak of World War I. He made 7 appearances during the war in a season that was completed, before football stopped. Following the resumption of football for the [[1919<U+2013>20 Football League|1919<U+2013>20 season]] he was unable to stake a regular place in the team and only made 4 appearances. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lfchistory.net/Players/Player/Profile/854 |title=Sam Speakman |publisher=LFC History |accessdate=23 March 2012 }}</ref>

